{"word":"φρουρέω","slug":"φρουρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φρουρέω</b></el> <el>(φρουρέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>φροῦρος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to keep watch</i> or <i>guard</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to watch, guard</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>στόμα φρουρεῖν εὔφημον</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> to keep silent, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be watched</i> or <i>guarded</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to watch for</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>φρ. τὸ χρέος</el> to <i>observe</i> one's duty, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, like <el>φυλάσσομαι</el>, <i>to be on one's guard against, beware of</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> in same sense, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}